<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12043c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12043c">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12043c"> 43(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ dark &amp; ungentle to / the sons of death</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The <cite>Tripartite Life</cite>, written by St. Evin, narrates the last moments of our Saint as follows:&mdash; / &ldquo;A just man, indeed, was this man <font color="green">[&ldquo;]</font> a true pilgrim, like Abraham <font color="green">[&ldquo;]</font> gentle, humble, merciful to the sons of life; dark, ungentle towards the sons of death <font color="green">[&ldquo;]</font>&rdquo; <small> Very Rev. Dean Kinane, <a name="TKSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TKSP"><cite title="source">St. Patrick: his life, his heroic virtues, his labours, and the fruits of his labours</cite></a>, (ed. unknown) 177-8</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
